{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":588,"text":"I'm a computer science professor,"},{"time":3619,"text":"and my area of expertise is"},{"time":5932,"text":"computer and information security."},{"time":8131,"text":"When I was in graduate school,"},{"time":10451,"text":"I had the opportunity to overhear my grandmother"},{"time":13052,"text":"describing to one of her fellow senior citizens"},{"time":17186,"text":"what I did for a living."},{"time":19555,"text":"Apparently, I was in charge of making sure that"},{"time":23117,"text":"no one stole the computers from the university. (Laughter)"},{"time":27017,"text":"And, you know, that's a perfectly reasonable thing"},{"time":29761,"text":"for her to think, because I told her I was working"},{"time":31681,"text":"in computer security,"},{"time":33188,"text":"and it was interesting to get her perspective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36785,"text":"But that's not the most ridiculous thing I've ever heard"},{"time":39402,"text":"anyone say about my work."},{"time":41419,"text":"The most ridiculous thing I ever heard is,"},{"time":43703,"text":"I was at a dinner party, and a woman heard"},{"time":46837,"text":"that I work in computer security,"},{"time":48620,"text":"and she asked me if -- she said her computer had been"},{"time":52137,"text":"infected by a virus, and she was very concerned that she"},{"time":55573,"text":"might get sick from it, that she could get this virus. (Laughter)"},{"time":59524,"text":"And I'm not a doctor, but I reassured her"},{"time":62467,"text":"that it was very, very unlikely that this would happen,"},{"time":65611,"text":"but if she felt more comfortable, she could be free to use"},{"time":68412,"text":"latex gloves when she was on the computer,"},{"time":70260,"text":"and there would be no harm whatsoever in that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73652,"text":"I'm going to get back to this notion of being able to get"},{"time":76159,"text":"a virus from your computer, in a serious way."},{"time":79667,"text":"What I'm going to talk to you about today"},{"time":81307,"text":"are some hacks, some real world cyberattacks that people"},{"time":86153,"text":"in my community, the academic research community,"},{"time":88707,"text":"have performed, which I don't think"},{"time":91501,"text":"most people know about,"},{"time":92709,"text":"and I think they're very interesting and scary,"},{"time":95737,"text":"and this talk is kind of a greatest hits"},{"time":98178,"text":"of the academic security community's hacks."},{"time":101169,"text":"None of the work is my work. It's all work"},{"time":103156,"text":"that my colleagues have done, and I actually asked them"},{"time":105330,"text":"for their slides and incorporated them into this talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107887,"text":"So the first one I'm going to talk about"},{"time":109629,"text":"are implanted medical devices."},{"time":112303,"text":"Now medical devices have come a long way technologically."},{"time":115343,"text":"You can see in 1926 the first pacemaker was invented."},{"time":119199,"text":"1960, the first internal pacemaker was implanted,"},{"time":122751,"text":"hopefully a little smaller than that one that you see there,"},{"time":125303,"text":"and the technology has continued to move forward."},{"time":128271,"text":"In 2006, we hit an important milestone from the perspective"},{"time":132904,"text":"of computer security."},{"time":136071,"text":"And why do I say that?"},{"time":137412,"text":"Because that's when implanted devices inside of people"},{"time":140302,"text":"started to have networking capabilities."},{"time":143047,"text":"One thing that brings us close to home is we look"},{"time":144927,"text":"at Dick Cheney's device, he had a device that"},{"time":147632,"text":"pumped blood from an aorta to another part of the heart,"},{"time":151501,"text":"and as you can see at the bottom there,"},{"time":152684,"text":"it was controlled by a computer controller,"},{"time":155693,"text":"and if you ever thought that software liability"},{"time":158210,"text":"was very important, get one of these inside of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161799,"text":"Now what a research team did was they got their hands"},{"time":165494,"text":"on what's called an ICD."},{"time":166914,"text":"This is a defibrillator, and this is a device"},{"time":168984,"text":"that goes into a person to control their heart rhythm,"},{"time":173320,"text":"and these have saved many lives."},{"time":175658,"text":"Well, in order to not have to open up the person"},{"time":178130,"text":"every time you want to reprogram their device"},{"time":180324,"text":"or do some diagnostics on it, they made the thing be able"},{"time":182779,"text":"to communicate wirelessly, and what this research team did"},{"time":185881,"text":"is they reverse engineered the wireless protocol,"},{"time":188491,"text":"and they built the device you see pictured here,"},{"time":190363,"text":"with a little antenna, that could talk the protocol"},{"time":193123,"text":"to the device, and thus control it."},{"time":197598,"text":"In order to make their experience real -- they were unable"},{"time":200287,"text":"to find any volunteers, and so they went"},{"time":202759,"text":"and they got some ground beef and some bacon"},{"time":204903,"text":"and they wrapped it all up to about the size"},{"time":206691,"text":"of a human being's area where the device would go,"},{"time":209489,"text":"and they stuck the device inside it"},{"time":210943,"text":"to perform their experiment somewhat realistically."},{"time":214075,"text":"They launched many, many successful attacks."},{"time":217095,"text":"One that I'll highlight here is changing the patient's name."},{"time":220151,"text":"I don't know why you would want to do that,"},{"time":221144,"text":"but I sure wouldn't want that done to me."},{"time":223248,"text":"And they were able to change therapies,"},{"time":225579,"text":"including disabling the device -- and this is with a real,"},{"time":228074,"text":"commercial, off-the-shelf device --"},{"time":229970,"text":"simply by performing reverse engineering and sending"},{"time":232016,"text":"wireless signals to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235005,"text":"There was a piece on NPR that some of these ICDs"},{"time":238585,"text":"could actually have their performance disrupted"},{"time":241007,"text":"simply by holding a pair of headphones onto them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244658,"text":"Now, wireless and the Internet"},{"time":246067,"text":"can improve health care greatly."},{"time":247719,"text":"There's several examples up on the screen"},{"time":249806,"text":"of situations where doctors are looking to implant devices"},{"time":252913,"text":"inside of people, and all of these devices now,"},{"time":255778,"text":"it's standard that they communicate wirelessly,"},{"time":258903,"text":"and I think this is great,"},{"time":260315,"text":"but without a full understanding of trustworthy computing,"},{"time":263420,"text":"and without understanding what attackers can do"},{"time":265827,"text":"and the security risks from the beginning,"},{"time":267974,"text":"there's a lot of danger in this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270364,"text":"Okay, let me shift gears and show you another target."},{"time":271841,"text":"I'm going to show you a few different targets like this,"},{"time":273929,"text":"and that's my talk. So we'll look at automobiles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276846,"text":"This is a car, and it has a lot of components,"},{"time":279742,"text":"a lot of electronics in it today."},{"time":281362,"text":"In fact, it's got many, many different computers inside of it,"},{"time":285739,"text":"more Pentiums than my lab did when I was in college,"},{"time":288894,"text":"and they're connected by a wired network."},{"time":292533,"text":"There's also a wireless network in the car,"},{"time":295964,"text":"which can be reached from many different ways."},{"time":299197,"text":"So there's Bluetooth, there's the FM and XM radio,"},{"time":302898,"text":"there's actually wi-fi, there's sensors in the wheels"},{"time":305718,"text":"that wirelessly communicate the tire pressure"},{"time":307871,"text":"to a controller on board."},{"time":309677,"text":"The modern car is a sophisticated multi-computer device."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314595,"text":"And what happens if somebody wanted to attack this?"},{"time":317917,"text":"Well, that's what the researchers"},{"time":319234,"text":"that I'm going to talk about today did."},{"time":321105,"text":"They basically stuck an attacker on the wired network"},{"time":324082,"text":"and on the wireless network."},{"time":326404,"text":"Now, they have two areas they can attack."},{"time":329103,"text":"One is short-range wireless, where you can actually"},{"time":331141,"text":"communicate with the device from nearby,"},{"time":332922,"text":"either through Bluetooth or wi-fi,"},{"time":335059,"text":"and the other is long-range, where you can communicate"},{"time":337233,"text":"with the car through the cellular network,"},{"time":339015,"text":"or through one of the radio stations."},{"time":340975,"text":"Think about it. When a car receives a radio signal,"},{"time":344024,"text":"it's processed by software."},{"time":346225,"text":"That software has to receive and decode the radio signal,"},{"time":349286,"text":"and then figure out what to do with it,"},{"time":350405,"text":"even if it's just music that it needs to play on the radio,"},{"time":353429,"text":"and that software that does that decoding,"},{"time":355697,"text":"if it has any bugs in it, could create a vulnerability"},{"time":358790,"text":"for somebody to hack the car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361825,"text":"The way that the researchers did this work is,"},{"time":364777,"text":"they read the software in the computer chips"},{"time":369000,"text":"that were in the car, and then they used sophisticated"},{"time":372193,"text":"reverse engineering tools"},{"time":373607,"text":"to figure out what that software did,"},{"time":375662,"text":"and then they found vulnerabilities in that software,"},{"time":378703,"text":"and then they built exploits to exploit those."},{"time":382049,"text":"They actually carried out their attack in real life."},{"time":384431,"text":"They bought two cars, and I guess"},{"time":385781,"text":"they have better budgets than I do."},{"time":388699,"text":"The first threat model was to see what someone could do"},{"time":391289,"text":"if an attacker actually got access"},{"time":393433,"text":"to the internal network on the car."},{"time":395486,"text":"Okay, so think of that as, someone gets to go to your car,"},{"time":398089,"text":"they get to mess around with it, and then they leave,"},{"time":400993,"text":"and now, what kind of trouble are you in?"},{"time":403361,"text":"The other threat model is that they contact you"},{"time":406153,"text":"in real time over one of the wireless networks"},{"time":408610,"text":"like the cellular, or something like that,"},{"time":410665,"text":"never having actually gotten physical access to your car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414665,"text":"This is what their setup looks like for the first model,"},{"time":417489,"text":"where you get to have access to the car."},{"time":419172,"text":"They put a laptop, and they connected to the diagnostic unit"},{"time":422559,"text":"on the in-car network, and they did all kinds of silly things,"},{"time":425498,"text":"like here's a picture of the speedometer"},{"time":428281,"text":"showing 140 miles an hour when the car's in park."},{"time":431097,"text":"Once you have control of the car's computers,"},{"time":433470,"text":"you can do anything."},{"time":434389,"text":"Now you might say, \"Okay, that's silly.\""},{"time":436005,"text":"Well, what if you make the car always say"},{"time":437664,"text":"it's going 20 miles an hour slower than it's actually going?"},{"time":440405,"text":"You might produce a lot of speeding tickets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":442947,"text":"Then they went out to an abandoned airstrip with two cars,"},{"time":446803,"text":"the target victim car and the chase car,"},{"time":449548,"text":"and they launched a bunch of other attacks."},{"time":452294,"text":"One of the things they were able to do from the chase car"},{"time":455060,"text":"is apply the brakes on the other car,"},{"time":457034,"text":"simply by hacking the computer."},{"time":458594,"text":"They were able to disable the brakes."},{"time":461025,"text":"They also were able to install malware that wouldn't kick in"},{"time":464203,"text":"and wouldn't trigger until the car was doing something like"},{"time":466628,"text":"going over 20 miles an hour, or something like that."},{"time":470374,"text":"The results are astonishing, and when they gave this talk,"},{"time":473132,"text":"even though they gave this talk at a conference"},{"time":474848,"text":"to a bunch of computer security researchers,"},{"time":476574,"text":"everybody was gasping."},{"time":478274,"text":"They were able to take over a bunch of critical computers"},{"time":481973,"text":"inside the car: the brakes computer, the lighting computer,"},{"time":485734,"text":"the engine, the dash, the radio, etc.,"},{"time":488561,"text":"and they were able to perform these on real commercial"},{"time":490854,"text":"cars that they purchased using the radio network."},{"time":493881,"text":"They were able to compromise every single one of the"},{"time":496884,"text":"pieces of software that controlled every single one"},{"time":499350,"text":"of the wireless capabilities of the car."},{"time":502365,"text":"All of these were implemented successfully."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504878,"text":"How would you steal a car in this model?"},{"time":507230,"text":"Well, you compromise the car by a buffer overflow"},{"time":510910,"text":"of vulnerability in the software, something like that."},{"time":513437,"text":"You use the GPS in the car to locate it."},{"time":515640,"text":"You remotely unlock the doors through the computer"},{"time":517835,"text":"that controls that, start the engine, bypass anti-theft,"},{"time":520973,"text":"and you've got yourself a car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522641,"text":"Surveillance was really interesting."},{"time":525128,"text":"The authors of the study have a video where they show"},{"time":528337,"text":"themselves taking over a car and then turning on"},{"time":530886,"text":"the microphone in the car, and listening in on the car"},{"time":533647,"text":"while tracking it via GPS on a map,"},{"time":536998,"text":"and so that's something that the drivers of the car"},{"time":538711,"text":"would never know was happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540879,"text":"Am I scaring you yet?"},{"time":543013,"text":"I've got a few more of these interesting ones."},{"time":544956,"text":"These are ones where I went to a conference,"},{"time":546789,"text":"and my mind was just blown, and I said,"},{"time":548722,"text":"\"I have to share this with other people.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":550548,"text":"This was Fabian Monrose's lab"},{"time":552171,"text":"at the University of North Carolina, and what they did was"},{"time":555627,"text":"something intuitive once you see it,"},{"time":557702,"text":"but kind of surprising."},{"time":559416,"text":"They videotaped people on a bus,"},{"time":561675,"text":"and then they post-processed the video."},{"time":564515,"text":"What you see here in number one is a"},{"time":566978,"text":"reflection in somebody's glasses of the smartphone"},{"time":571361,"text":"that they're typing in."},{"time":572786,"text":"They wrote software to stabilize --"},{"time":574761,"text":"even though they were on a bus"},{"time":576126,"text":"and maybe someone's holding their phone at an angle --"},{"time":579337,"text":"to stabilize the phone, process it, and"},{"time":581707,"text":"you may know on your smartphone, when you type"},{"time":583592,"text":"a password, the keys pop out a little bit, and they were able"},{"time":586531,"text":"to use that to reconstruct what the person was typing,"},{"time":589371,"text":"and had a language model for detecting typing."},{"time":593692,"text":"What was interesting is, by videotaping on a bus,"},{"time":596027,"text":"they were able to produce exactly what people"},{"time":598156,"text":"on their smartphones were typing,"},{"time":600307,"text":"and then they had a surprising result, which is that"},{"time":602567,"text":"their software had not only done it for their target,"},{"time":605331,"text":"but other people who accidentally happened"},{"time":606734,"text":"to be in the picture, they were able to produce"},{"time":608820,"text":"what those people had been typing, and that was kind of"},{"time":611547,"text":"an accidental artifact of what their software was doing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615164,"text":"I'll show you two more. One is P25 radios."},{"time":619467,"text":"P25 radios are used by law enforcement"},{"time":622267,"text":"and all kinds of government agencies"},{"time":625674,"text":"and people in combat to communicate,"},{"time":627410,"text":"and there's an encryption option on these phones."},{"time":630243,"text":"This is what the phone looks like. It's not really a phone."},{"time":632971,"text":"It's more of a two-way radio."},{"time":634177,"text":"Motorola makes the most widely used one, and you can see"},{"time":637499,"text":"that they're used by Secret Service, they're used in combat,"},{"time":640148,"text":"it's a very, very common standard in the U.S. and elsewhere."},{"time":643250,"text":"So one question the researchers asked themselves is,"},{"time":645555,"text":"could you block this thing, right?"},{"time":648259,"text":"Could you run a denial-of-service,"},{"time":649842,"text":"because these are first responders?"},{"time":651666,"text":"So, would a terrorist organization want to black out the"},{"time":653467,"text":"ability of police and fire to communicate at an emergency?"},{"time":657955,"text":"They found that there's this GirlTech device used for texting"},{"time":661027,"text":"that happens to operate at the same exact frequency"},{"time":663745,"text":"as the P25, and they built what they called"},{"time":666016,"text":"My First Jammer. (Laughter)"},{"time":670350,"text":"If you look closely at this device,"},{"time":672728,"text":"it's got a switch for encryption or cleartext."},{"time":676358,"text":"Let me advance the slide, and now I'll go back."},{"time":679408,"text":"You see the difference?"},{"time":681955,"text":"This is plain text. This is encrypted."},{"time":684512,"text":"There's one little dot that shows up on the screen,"},{"time":687069,"text":"and one little tiny turn of the switch."},{"time":689154,"text":"And so the researchers asked themselves, \"I wonder how"},{"time":691058,"text":"many times very secure, important, sensitive conversations"},{"time":695315,"text":"are happening on these two-way radios where they forget"},{"time":696938,"text":"to encrypt and they don't notice that they didn't encrypt?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":699848,"text":"So they bought a scanner. These are perfectly legal"},{"time":703187,"text":"and they run at the frequency of the P25,"},{"time":706645,"text":"and what they did is they hopped around frequencies"},{"time":708412,"text":"and they wrote software to listen in."},{"time":710922,"text":"If they found encrypted communication, they stayed"},{"time":713556,"text":"on that channel and they wrote down, that's a channel"},{"time":715242,"text":"that these people communicate in,"},{"time":717030,"text":"these law enforcement agencies,"},{"time":718652,"text":"and they went to 20 metropolitan areas and listened in"},{"time":722043,"text":"on conversations that were happening at those frequencies."},{"time":725518,"text":"They found that in every metropolitan area,"},{"time":728757,"text":"they would capture over 20 minutes a day"},{"time":730911,"text":"of cleartext communication."},{"time":733286,"text":"And what kind of things were people talking about?"},{"time":735286,"text":"Well, they found the names and information"},{"time":736770,"text":"about confidential informants. They found information"},{"time":739622,"text":"that was being recorded in wiretaps,"},{"time":741824,"text":"a bunch of crimes that were being discussed,"},{"time":744534,"text":"sensitive information."},{"time":745696,"text":"It was mostly law enforcement and criminal."},{"time":749059,"text":"They went and reported this to the law enforcement"},{"time":750893,"text":"agencies, after anonymizing it,"},{"time":752916,"text":"and the vulnerability here is simply the user interface"},{"time":755916,"text":"wasn't good enough. If you're talking"},{"time":757310,"text":"about something really secure and sensitive, it should"},{"time":760126,"text":"be really clear to you that this conversation is encrypted."},{"time":763419,"text":"That one's pretty easy to fix."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765305,"text":"The last one I thought was really, really cool,"},{"time":766974,"text":"and I just had to show it to you, it's probably not something"},{"time":769787,"text":"that you're going to lose sleep over"},{"time":770792,"text":"like the cars or the defibrillators,"},{"time":772583,"text":"but it's stealing keystrokes."},{"time":775606,"text":"Now, we've all looked at smartphones upside down."},{"time":778353,"text":"Every security expert wants to hack a smartphone,"},{"time":780543,"text":"and we tend to look at the USB port, the GPS for tracking,"},{"time":785155,"text":"the camera, the microphone, but no one up till this point"},{"time":788363,"text":"had looked at the accelerometer."},{"time":789943,"text":"The accelerometer is the thing that determines"},{"time":791590,"text":"the vertical orientation of the smartphone."},{"time":795084,"text":"And so they had a simple setup."},{"time":796501,"text":"They put a smartphone next to a keyboard,"},{"time":799259,"text":"and they had people type, and then their goal was"},{"time":801971,"text":"to use the vibrations that were created by typing"},{"time":804827,"text":"to measure the change in the accelerometer reading"},{"time":809067,"text":"to determine what the person had been typing."},{"time":812243,"text":"Now, when they tried this on an iPhone 3GS,"},{"time":814819,"text":"this is a graph of the perturbations that were created"},{"time":817588,"text":"by the typing, and you can see that it's very difficult"},{"time":820829,"text":"to tell when somebody was typing or what they were typing,"},{"time":823907,"text":"but the iPhone 4 greatly improved the accelerometer,"},{"time":826997,"text":"and so the same measurement"},{"time":830477,"text":"produced this graph."},{"time":832309,"text":"Now that gave you a lot of information while someone"},{"time":834795,"text":"was typing, and what they did then is used advanced"},{"time":838036,"text":"artificial intelligence techniques called machine learning"},{"time":841043,"text":"to have a training phase,"},{"time":842474,"text":"and so they got most likely grad students"},{"time":844710,"text":"to type in a whole lot of things, and to learn,"},{"time":848499,"text":"to have the system use the machine learning tools that"},{"time":851267,"text":"were available to learn what it is that the people were typing"},{"time":854130,"text":"and to match that up"},{"time":856957,"text":"with the measurements in the accelerometer."},{"time":859434,"text":"And then there's the attack phase, where you get"},{"time":861069,"text":"somebody to type something in, you don't know what it was,"},{"time":863880,"text":"but you use your model that you created"},{"time":865177,"text":"in the training phase to figure out what they were typing."},{"time":868619,"text":"They had pretty good success. This is an article from the USA Today."},{"time":872103,"text":"They typed in, \"The Illinois Supreme Court has ruled"},{"time":874712,"text":"that Rahm Emanuel is eligible to run for Mayor of Chicago\""},{"time":877674,"text":"— see, I tied it in to the last talk —"},{"time":879028,"text":"\"and ordered him to stay on the ballot.\""},{"time":881146,"text":"Now, the system is interesting, because it produced"},{"time":883917,"text":"\"Illinois Supreme\" and then it wasn't sure."},{"time":886803,"text":"The model produced a bunch of options,"},{"time":888753,"text":"and this is the beauty of some of the A.I. techniques,"},{"time":891462,"text":"is that computers are good at some things,"},{"time":893712,"text":"humans are good at other things,"},{"time":895246,"text":"take the best of both and let the humans solve this one."},{"time":897177,"text":"Don't waste computer cycles."},{"time":898559,"text":"A human's not going to think it's the Supreme might."},{"time":900695,"text":"It's the Supreme Court, right?"},{"time":902435,"text":"And so, together we're able to reproduce typing"},{"time":904965,"text":"simply by measuring the accelerometer."},{"time":907914,"text":"Why does this matter? Well, in the Android platform,"},{"time":911416,"text":"for example, the developers have a manifest"},{"time":915564,"text":"where every device on there, the microphone, etc.,"},{"time":918148,"text":"has to register if you're going to use it"},{"time":920104,"text":"so that hackers can't take over it,"},{"time":922420,"text":"but nobody controls the accelerometer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":925528,"text":"So what's the point? You can leave your iPhone next to"},{"time":927744,"text":"someone's keyboard, and just leave the room,"},{"time":929850,"text":"and then later recover what they did,"},{"time":931489,"text":"even without using the microphone."},{"time":933200,"text":"If someone is able to put malware on your iPhone,"},{"time":935374,"text":"they could then maybe get the typing that you do"},{"time":938222,"text":"whenever you put your iPhone next to your keyboard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940543,"text":"There's several other notable attacks that unfortunately"},{"time":942814,"text":"I don't have time to go into, but the one that I wanted"},{"time":944945,"text":"to point out was a group from the University of Michigan"},{"time":947222,"text":"which was able to take voting machines,"},{"time":949663,"text":"the Sequoia AVC Edge DREs that"},{"time":952161,"text":"were going to be used in New Jersey in the election"},{"time":953716,"text":"that were left in a hallway, and put Pac-Man on it."},{"time":955877,"text":"So they ran the Pac-Man game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":959500,"text":"What does this all mean?"},{"time":961247,"text":"Well, I think that society tends to adopt technology"},{"time":964894,"text":"really quickly. I love the next coolest gadget."},{"time":967718,"text":"But it's very important, and these researchers are showing,"},{"time":970332,"text":"that the developers of these things"},{"time":971692,"text":"need to take security into account from the very beginning,"},{"time":974557,"text":"and need to realize that they may have a threat model,"},{"time":977342,"text":"but the attackers may not be nice enough"},{"time":979804,"text":"to limit themselves to that threat model,"},{"time":981581,"text":"and so you need to think outside of the box."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984118,"text":"What we can do is be aware"},{"time":985696,"text":"that devices can be compromised,"},{"time":988175,"text":"and anything that has software in it"},{"time":989874,"text":"is going to be vulnerable. It's going to have bugs."},{"time":992523,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}